<br>
Try to find places where other people don't go to maximize camp bonus.  The front room in Tepok for early 20s and Barfog for 20s/30s were good to me, for example (undead monks are crunchy *and* respawn almost instantly).<br>
<br>
Also, I've found that when soloing, blues can be better than yellows, if you can kill without being hit much and without styling.  This is, I think, really only viable i the 40s, when you can put more points in parry, but I spent a good chunk of my 40s in the Dales killing constructs.  With First Aid I, I was able to kill 10-15 mobs without sitting down, which I believe has to be faster than yellow-sit-for-end-yellow soloing. (plus it game me good Drac faction, which is actually useful at times) <p>Acus TwinHammer<br>
4x Crush Merc, Pellinor</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gwerraldarkmorn>Gwerral Darkmorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#000000>(2/12/03 7:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=37.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing Merc</span><hr size=1> I'd also reccommend the hollow men in Snowdonia (coming to Barfog in 1.60) from late 30s through low 40s.  Darkness Falls at the rocots or the Cook's room is decent experience and really nice coin if you are able to get into the Falls.  And blue or green linked monsters in the Isles are nice as well.  (The drakorans wandering around outside of Avalon City were nice for a while.)  Up until about 45, I could earn better xp hunting by myself or in a very small group than in a group of 8 at one of the more typical hunting spots.<br>
<br>
Personally, I like to hunt out in the frontiers: there is always a camp bonus, there is a keep bonus if you are close enough to one, and you will be close if needed for defense.  Unfortunately, my homeland has been very active lately and I haven't been able to go out except on defenses and keep retakes.  &lt;sighs&gt;<br>
<br>
Of course, if you have access to Avalon, you could always go on a few sentry &quot;raids&quot; (ie, zergs).  They have almost completely replaced trees for getting to 50 on Percival.  It's not the most interesting hunting, but it got me to 50 (kicking and screaming, mind you). <p>Gwerral Darkmorn<br>
